{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":975,"text":"The Kraken, a beast so terrifying"},{"time":4011,"text":"it was said to devour men and ships and whales,"},{"time":7108,"text":"and so enormous it could be mistaken for an island."},{"time":11035,"text":"In assessing the merits of such tales,"},{"time":13291,"text":"it's probably wise to keep in mind that old sailor's saw"},{"time":16176,"text":"that the only difference between a fairytale and a sea story"},{"time":19799,"text":"is a fairytale begins, \"Once upon a time,\""},{"time":22436,"text":"and a sea story begins, \"This ain't no shit.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":27669,"text":"Every fish that gets away"},{"time":29447,"text":"grows with every telling of the tale."},{"time":31595,"text":"Nevertheless, there are giants in the ocean,"},{"time":34082,"text":"and we now have video proof,"},{"time":36111,"text":"as those of you that saw the Discovery Channel documentary are no doubt aware."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40733,"text":"I was one of the three scientists on this expedition"},{"time":43370,"text":"that took place last summer off Japan."},{"time":45566,"text":"I'm the short one."},{"time":48062,"text":"The other two are Dr. Tsunemi Kubodera and Dr. Steve O'Shea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52120,"text":"I owe my participation in this now-historic event"},{"time":55650,"text":"to TED."},{"time":57456,"text":"In 2010, there was a TED event called Mission Blue"},{"time":60531,"text":"held aboard the Lindblad Explorer in the Galapagos"},{"time":63265,"text":"as part of the fulfillment of Sylvia Earle's TED wish."},{"time":67107,"text":"I spoke about a new way of exploring the ocean,"},{"time":69896,"text":"one that focuses on attracting animals instead of scaring them away."},{"time":74673,"text":"Mike deGruy was also invited,"},{"time":76969,"text":"and he spoke with great passion about his love of the ocean,"},{"time":80524,"text":"and he also talked to me about applying my approach"},{"time":82937,"text":"to something he's been involved with for a very long time,"},{"time":85593,"text":"which is the hunt for the giant squid."},{"time":89027,"text":"It was Mike that got me invited to the squid summit,"},{"time":92907,"text":"a gathering of squid experts at the Discovery Channel"},{"time":97032,"text":"that summer during Shark Week. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":101821,"text":"I gave a talk on unobtrusive viewing"},{"time":104237,"text":"and optical luring of deep sea squid"},{"time":106780,"text":"in which I emphasized the importance"},{"time":108557,"text":"of using quiet, unobtrusive platforms for exploration."},{"time":113807,"text":"This came out of hundreds of dives I have made,"},{"time":116532,"text":"farting around in the dark"},{"time":118858,"text":"using these platforms,"},{"time":121636,"text":"and my impression that I saw more animals"},{"time":125219,"text":"working from the submersible"},{"time":127100,"text":"than I did with either of the remote-operated vehicles."},{"time":130020,"text":"But that could just be because the submersible has a wider field of view."},{"time":133390,"text":"But I also felt like I saw more animals"},{"time":135079,"text":"working with the Tiburon than the Ventana,"},{"time":136930,"text":"two vehicles with the same field of view"},{"time":139115,"text":"but different propulsion systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141153,"text":"So my suspicion was that it might have something to do with the amount of noise they make."},{"time":145184,"text":"So I set up a hydrophone on the bottom of the ocean,"},{"time":147440,"text":"and I had each of these fly by at the same speed and distance"},{"time":150600,"text":"and recorded the sound they made."},{"time":153032,"text":"The Johnson Sea-Link -- (whirring noise) --"},{"time":154669,"text":"which you can probably just barely hear here,"},{"time":157264,"text":"uses electric thrusters -- very, very quiet."},{"time":160864,"text":"The Tiburon also uses electric powered thrusters."},{"time":164219,"text":"It's also pretty quiet, but a bit noisier. (Louder whirring noise)"},{"time":169298,"text":"But most deep-diving ROVs these days use hydraulics"},{"time":172501,"text":"and they sound like the Ventana. (Loud beeping noise)"},{"time":175939,"text":"I think that's got to be scaring a lot of animals away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179365,"text":"So for the deep sea squid hunt,"},{"time":181858,"text":"I proposed using an optical lure"},{"time":184015,"text":"attached to a camera platform"},{"time":186175,"text":"with no thrusters, no motors,"},{"time":190943,"text":"just a battery-powered camera,"},{"time":193552,"text":"and the only illumination coming from red light"},{"time":196572,"text":"that's invisible to most deep-sea animals"},{"time":199064,"text":"that are adapted to see primarily blue."},{"time":201756,"text":"That's visible to our eye,"},{"time":203018,"text":"but it's the equivalent of infrared in the deep sea."},{"time":206359,"text":"So this camera platform, which we called the Medusa,"},{"time":209200,"text":"could just be thrown off the back of the ship,"},{"time":211329,"text":"attached to a float at the surface with over 2,000 feet of line,"},{"time":216915,"text":"it would just float around passively carried by the currents,"},{"time":220994,"text":"and the only light visible to the animals in the deep"},{"time":225391,"text":"would be the blue light of the optical lure,"},{"time":229378,"text":"which we called the electronic jellyfish, or e-jelly,"},{"time":233158,"text":"because it was designed to imitate"},{"time":236018,"text":"the bioluminescent display"},{"time":238274,"text":"of the common deep sea jellyfish Atolla."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241619,"text":"Now, this pinwheel of light that the Atolla produces"},{"time":245180,"text":"is known as a bioluminescent burglar alarm"},{"time":248163,"text":"and is a form of defense."},{"time":250441,"text":"The reason that the electronic jellyfish worked as a lure"},{"time":253622,"text":"is not because giant squid eat jellyfish,"},{"time":256525,"text":"but it's because this jellyfish only resorts to producing this light"},{"time":260954,"text":"when it's being chewed on by a predator"},{"time":263331,"text":"and its only hope for escape"},{"time":266010,"text":"may be to attract the attention of a larger predator"},{"time":268985,"text":"that will attack its attacker"},{"time":271047,"text":"and thereby afford it an opportunity for escape."},{"time":273590,"text":"It's a scream for help, a last-ditch attempt for escape,"},{"time":277482,"text":"and a common form of defense in the deep sea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280890,"text":"The approach worked."},{"time":283003,"text":"Whereas all previous expeditions had failed to garner"},{"time":286514,"text":"a single video glimpse of the giant,"},{"time":288962,"text":"we managed six, and the first triggered wild excitement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293627,"text":"Edith Widder (on video): Oh my God. Oh my God! Are you kidding me?Other scientists: Oh ho ho! That's just hanging there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306845,"text":"EW: It was like it was teasing us, doing a kind of fan dance --"},{"time":309981,"text":"now you see me, now you don't --"},{"time":312026,"text":"and we had four such teasing appearances,"},{"time":315029,"text":"and then on the fifth, it came in and totally wowed us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320438,"text":"(Music) Narrator: (Speaking in Japanese)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":324711,"text":"Scientists: Ooh. Bang! Oh my God! Whoa!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":336999,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":339253,"text":"EW: The full monty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344107,"text":"What really wowed me about that"},{"time":345452,"text":"was the way it came in up over the e-jelly"},{"time":347626,"text":"and then attacked the enormous thing next to it,"},{"time":349946,"text":"which I think it mistook for the predator on the e-jelly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":353252,"text":"But even more incredible was the footage shot"},{"time":355671,"text":"from the Triton submersible."},{"time":358316,"text":"What was not mentioned in the Discovery documentary"},{"time":361100,"text":"was that the bait squid that Dr. Kubodera used,"},{"time":364546,"text":"a one-meter long diamondback squid"},{"time":368148,"text":"had a light attached to it, a squid jig"},{"time":370860,"text":"of the type that longline fishermen use,"},{"time":373444,"text":"and I think it was this light"},{"time":375482,"text":"that brought the giant in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378031,"text":"Now, what you're seeing"},{"time":379496,"text":"is the intensified camera's view under red light,"},{"time":384594,"text":"and that's all Dr. Kubodera could see when the giant comes in here."},{"time":388716,"text":"And then he got so excited,"},{"time":391171,"text":"he turned on his flashlight because he wanted to see better,"},{"time":394666,"text":"and the giant didn't run away,"},{"time":396850,"text":"so he risked turning on the white lights on the submersible,"},{"time":400091,"text":"bringing a creature of legend"},{"time":402627,"text":"from the misty history into high-resolution video."},{"time":407598,"text":"It was absolutely breathtaking,"},{"time":410866,"text":"and had this animal had its feeding tentacles intact"},{"time":413795,"text":"and fully extended,"},{"time":415260,"text":"it would have been as tall as a two-story house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418512,"text":"How could something that big"},{"time":421171,"text":"live in our ocean and yet remain unfilmed until now?"},{"time":425771,"text":"We've only explored about five percent of our ocean."},{"time":429395,"text":"There are great discoveries yet to be made down there,"},{"time":432531,"text":"fantastic creatures representing millions of years of evolution"},{"time":437153,"text":"and possibly bioactive compounds"},{"time":439250,"text":"that could benefit us in ways that we can't even yet imagine."},{"time":443065,"text":"Yet we have spent only a tiny fraction"},{"time":446113,"text":"of the money on ocean exploration"},{"time":449482,"text":"that we've spent on space exploration."},{"time":451889,"text":"We need a NASA-like organization for ocean exploration,"},{"time":455534,"text":"because we need to be exploring and protecting"},{"time":458369,"text":"our life support systems here on Earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460961,"text":"We need — thank you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":467193,"text":"Exploration is the engine that drives innovation."},{"time":470047,"text":"Innovation drives economic growth."},{"time":473018,"text":"So let's all go exploring,"},{"time":474541,"text":"but let's do it in a way that doesn't scare the animals away,"},{"time":477642,"text":"or, as Mike deGruy once said,"},{"time":479975,"text":"\"If you want to get away from it all"},{"time":481761,"text":"and see something you've never seen,"},{"time":483375,"text":"or have an excellent chance of seeing something that no one's ever seen,"},{"time":486960,"text":"get in a sub.\""},{"time":488490,"text":"He should have been with us for this adventure."},{"time":490696,"text":"We miss him."},{"time":492503,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}